  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Acute kidney injury (AKI) is a common clinical syndrome, especially patients in the hospital.
      AKI has become a huge medical burden in China. Little information is available about this
      disease burden in our country. The investigators aimed to evaluate the burden of AKI and to
      analyze the related risk factors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The investigators launch a nationwide of all patients, who were admitted to hospital from
      2011-2016. Patients were diagnosed on the basis of changes in serum creatinine by the
      laboratory information system. The investigators assessed rates of AKI according to the
      criteria of 2012 Kidney Disease Improving Global Outcomes (KDIGO).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
